skyboxTime.title: Skybox Time
skyboxTime.description: Set the target skybox time that will be set on entity initialize.

pauseSkyboxCubemap.title: Pause Skybox Cubemap
pauseSkyboxCubemap.description: If selected and the skybox is rendering a real time cubemap, it will pause when the animation is not playing.

transitionSpeed.title: Transition Speed
transitionSpeed.description: Set the animation speed when changing the skybox time. Set to 0 for instantaneous updates

amount.title: Amount
amount.description: The amount of chromatic aberration applied.

normals.title: Normals
normals.description: Set the normals direction for each axis (-1 to 1).

template.title: Template
template.description: Reference a template asset to automatically instantiate on initialize.

waterPlane.title: Water Plane
waterPlane.description: If selected the effect will not render beneath this Y plane. Requires reload.

waterY.title: Water Y
waterY.description: If waterPlane is enabled, this value defines the Y position of the plane cutoff.

infiniteSurface.title: Infinite Surface
infiniteSurface.description: If selected the water surface will follow the active camera to give the illusion of an infinite water surface. Useful for sea and ocean effects.

depthOpacity.title: Depth Opacity
depthOpacity.description: Sets the amount of opacity the water will have as it gets deeper.

causticsOpacity.title: Caustics Opacity
causticsOpacity.description: Sets the amount of caustics effects the water will have as it gets deeper.

causticsIntensity.title: Caustics Intensity
causticsIntensity.description: Sets the intensity of the caustics effect.

causticsTiling.title: Caustics Tiling
causticsTiling.description: Sets the tiling of the caustics effect.

shoreOpacity.title: Shore Opacity
shoreOpacity.description: Sets the amount of shore effects the water will have as it gets deeper.

shoreIntensity.title: Shore Intensity
shoreIntensity.description: Sets the intensity of the shore effect.

shoreTiling.title: Shore Tiling
shoreTiling.description: Sets the tiling of the shore effect.

shoreFrequency.title: Shore Frequency
shoreFrequency.description: Sets the animation speed of shore effects on the water.

flowMapAsset.title: Flow Map
flowMapAsset.description: The flow map used to simulate the water flow effects.

flowFrequency.title: Flow Frequency
flowFrequency.description: Sets the animation speed of flow effects on the water.

causticsMapAsset.title: Caustics Map
causticsMapAsset.description: The caustics map used to simulate the water caustics effects.

reflectionsIntensity.title: Reflections Intensity
reflectionsIntensity.description: Sets the intensity of the reflections map.

underwaterFogDensity.title: Underwater Fog Density
underwaterFogDensity.description: Sets the intensity of the scene fog when the active camera is under the water surface. Set to 0.0 to disable this check.

activeCameras.title: Active Cameras
activeCameras.description: A list of cameras that render the water model, used to enable depth access to these cameras.

specularIntensity.title: Specular Intensity
specularIntensity.description: Sets the intensity of the specular highlights.

specularColor.title: Specular Color
specularColor.description: Sets the color of the specular highlights.

refractionOpacity.title: Refraction Opacity
refractionOpacity.description: Sets the amount of opacity the refraction effect will have as it gets deeper.

refractionIntensity.title: Refraction Intensity
refractionIntensity.description: Sets the intensity of the refraction map.

reflectionsBumpiness.title: Reflections Bumpiness
reflectionsBumpiness.description: Sets the intensity of the reflections bumpiness.

refractionBumpiness.title: Refraction Bumpiness
refractionBumpiness.description: Sets the intensity of the refraction bumpiness.

waterScale.title: Water Scale
waterScale.description: The scale of the water surface (texture tiling).

vertexWaves.title: Vertex Waves
vertexWaves.description: If selected the vertices of the water surface will animate to simulate waves. Requires a water plane with enough triangles per unit. Requires application reload.

wavesFrequency.title: Waves Frequency
wavesFrequency.description: The frequency of the sin/cos of the vertex waves.

wavesAmplitude.title: Waves Amplitude
wavesAmplitude.description: The amplitude of the sin/cos of the vertex waves.

wavesDepthMinMax.title: Waves Depth Min Max
wavesDepthMinMax.description: The min/max values to clamp the minimum and maximum wave height based on the water depth.

specularBlinking.title: Specular Blinking
specularBlinking.description: If a value > 0 is provided the specular highlights will blink based on that frequency.

renderSurface.title: Render Surface
renderSurface.description: If a uranusEffectsRenderSurface entity is referenced the material will use the depth from the surface to improve the look of several effects.

templates.title: Templates
templates.description: A list of templates that instances will be spawned from.

dataFile.title: Data File
dataFile.description: A JSON file that contains an one dimension data array that should conform to the selected format.

playcanvasToken.title: Playcanvas Token
playcanvasToken.description: A valid Playcanvas Rest API access token to be used for updating the data holder file if required.

spawnEntities.title: Spawn Entities
spawnEntities.description: If selected an entity will be spawned for each instance, otherwise buffers will be passed to the instancer which is more performance.

spawnEditCells.title: Spawn Edit Cells
spawnEditCells.description: If selected instances will be sorted in world positionwed cells to allow for realtime editing. If running in editor this setting is always set to true. This setting works only with Spawn Entities set to false.

useBaseMatrix.title: Use Base Matrix
useBaseMatrix.description: If set to true the base template entity matrix will be used for instancing and any internal hierarchy transformations will not be preserved. This offers a performance optimization.

singleInstance.title: Single Instance
singleInstance.description: If set to true all instances will be added in a single batch action resulting in increased performance. This disables editing of the instances.

seed.title: Seed
seed.description: Seed to be used for any random number generation, if required. Use 0 for a different random seed on each run.

templateFormat.title: Template Format
templateFormat.description: If set to yes the template format is expected to be included in the dataset, otherwise a random one will be generated.

schema.name: precisionX
schema.description: Number of decimal points used by this number when saving data.

schema.name: precisionY
schema.description: Number of decimal points used by this number when saving data.

schema.name: precisionZ
schema.description: Number of decimal points used by this number when saving data.

positionFormat.title: Position Format
positionFormat.description: Define which position elements to be parsed from data. Omitting elements can reduce the size of the data file.

schema.name: precisionX
schema.description: Number of decimal points used by this number when saving data.

schema.name: precisionY
schema.description: Number of decimal points used by this number when saving data.

schema.name: precisionZ
schema.description: Number of decimal points used by this number when saving data.

rotationFormat.title: Rotation Format
rotationFormat.description: Define which rotation elements to be parsed from data. Omitting elements can reduce the size of the data file.

schema.name: precisionX
schema.description: Number of decimal points used by this number when saving data.

schema.name: precisionY
schema.description: Number of decimal points used by this number when saving data.

schema.name: precisionZ
schema.description: Number of decimal points used by this number when saving data.

scaleFormat.title: Scale Format
scaleFormat.description: Define which scale elements to be parsed from data. Omitting elements can reduce the size of the data file.

randomPosition.title: Random Position
randomPosition.description: Calculate a random position per axis between the min/max limit provided. If 0,0 is provided no random position will be calculated.

randomRotation.title: Random Rotation
randomRotation.description: Calculate a random rotation per axis between the min/max limit provided (range 0-360). If 0,0 is provided no random rotation will be calculated.

schema.name: uniform
schema.title: Uniform
schema.description: If selected a uniform scale will be calculated for all three axis from the X random field.

schema.name: step
schema.title: Step
schema.description: If a value larger than 0 is provided each random scale will be rounded to the closest number based on this step.

randomScale.title: Random Scale
randomScale.description: Calculate a random scale per axis between the min/max limit provided. If 0,0 is provided no random scale will be calculated.

fadeIn.title: Fade In
fadeIn.description: If selected the effect will fade in at that distance, instead of fading out. Requires material reload.

fadeCamera.title: Fade Camera
fadeCamera.description: If a camera entity is provided the fade distance will be calculated from the entity world position. If none is provided then the world view position from the uranusInstancer will be used instead (this will work for instanced models only).

playerEntity.title: Player Entity
playerEntity.description: The player entity to enable VR on.

controllerEntity.title: Controller Entity
controllerEntity.description: VR controller to be spawned for each input source.

qualityPreset.title: Quality Preset
qualityPreset.description: If a quality preset is provided, it will be automatically enabled as soon as VR mode is enabled.

video.title: Video
video.description: MP4 video asset to play back on this video texture.

videoUrl.title: Video Url
videoUrl.description: Instead of passing a video asset you can add a remote url for video playback..

localServerUrl.title: Local Server Url
localServerUrl.description: The local server connection url (optional to be used with isLocal).

isLocal.title: Is Local
isLocal.description: If selected the client will connect to the local server.

schema.name: serverUrl
schema.title: Server Url
schema.description: The remote server connection url.

schema.name: chance
schema.title: Chance
schema.description: The remote server chance to be selected between other same region servers. Use to direct traffic to larger servers.

schema.name: region
schema.title: Region
schema.description: The regions this server url will be used for. This check uses internally the current timezone to match the user to a region. Leave empty to bypass this check and use this server globally. If a user is coming from a non listed region, one will be randomnly selected.

serverRemoteList.title: Server Remote List
serverRemoteList.description: Optionally reference a remote .json file that contains server info, instead of hardcoding them with the build.

spawnAreas.title: Spawn Areas
spawnAreas.description: A list of one or more entities to define the spawn areas. Each entity should have a box collider attached.

spawnEntities.title: Spawn Entities
spawnEntities.description: The entity to be positioned inside the spawn area.

spawnAreasTag.title: Spawn Areas Tag
spawnAreasTag.description: Instead of referencing area entities directly, you can use a tag to let the script find them on spawn time.

faceAngles.title: Face Angles
faceAngles.description: Set a minimum and maximum angle, in world units, to automatically face the entities towards.

faceCamera.title: Face Camera
faceCamera.description: If checked the script willa attempt to find a child camera entity to rotate, instead of the spawn entity.

bypassIfEnabled.title: Bypass If Enabled
bypassIfEnabled.description: Bypass and don't teleport the controller if it's already enabled.

onSpawn.title: On Spawn
onSpawn.description: If an event name is provided the script will execute as soon as this event is fired.

schema.name: maskMap
schema.title: Mask Map
schema.description: If a texture channel has been selected as mask reference the texture mask here.

moveSpeed.title: Move Speed
moveSpeed.description: The move speed of the character.

sprintSpeed.title: Sprint Speed
sprintSpeed.description: The sprint speed of the character. Set to 0.0 to disable sprinting.

gravity.title: Gravity
gravity.description: Extra gravity applied to the player in addition to the scene gravity.

jumpTimeout.title: Jump Timeout
jumpTimeout.description: Time required to pass before being able to jump again. Set to 0.0 to be able to instantly jump again.

fallTimeout.title: Ground Fall Timeout
fallTimeout.description: Time required to pass before entering the fall state while on ground. Useful for walking down stairs.

groundedOffset.title: Grounded Offset
groundedOffset.description: The threshold in world units for the grounded property, useful to simulate movement in rough terrain.

topClamp.title: Top Clamp
topClamp.description: The maximum value in angle degrees for the camera upwards movement.

bottomClamp.title: Bottom Clamp
bottomClamp.description: The maximum value in angle degrees for the camera downwards movement.

cameraAngleOverride.title: Camera Angle Override
cameraAngleOverride.description: Additional degress to override the camera. Useful for fine tuning camera position when locked.

lockCameraPosition.title: Lock Camera Position
lockCameraPosition.description: If selected camera movement will be locked in all axis.

camera.title: Camera
camera.description: The camera entity used for this player controller.

model.title: Model
model.description: The model entity used for this player controller.

sprintByDefault.title: Sprint By Default
sprintByDefault.description: If selected the default movement speed will be sprint.

touchRadius.title: Touch Radius
touchRadius.description: The radius of the virtual joystick.

swimSpeed.title: Swim Speed
swimSpeed.description: The swimming speed of the character.

waterLevel.title: Water Level
waterLevel.description: The global water level, if the player falls below this it will automatically enter swimming mode.

touchSprintThreshold.title: Touch Sprint Threshold
touchSprintThreshold.description: Set the threshold at which the touch joystick will switch from walking to sprinting.

cameraWaterOffset.title: Camera Water Offset
cameraWaterOffset.description: If a value > 0 is provided the camera will stay above the water surface by that offset.

doubleTapInterval.title: Double Tap Interval
doubleTapInterval.description: The time in milliseconds between two taps of the right virtual joystick for a double tap to register. A double tap will trigger a jump. Set to 0.0 to disable double tapping for jumping.

lockPlayerPosition.title: Lock Player Position
lockPlayerPosition.description: If selected player movement will be locked in all axis.

mousePointerLock.title: Mouse Pointer Lock
mousePointerLock.description: If selected the mouse pointer will be locked on click.

canFly.title: Can Fly
canFly.description: If selected the player will fly when double jumping.

flyFallTimeout.title: Fly Fall Timeout
flyFallTimeout.description: Time required to pass before entering the fall state while on hovering on air.

flySpeed.title: Fly Speed
flySpeed.description: The flying speed of the character.

flyClimbRatio.title: Fly Climb Ratio
flyClimbRatio.description: The vertical flying speed climb and descend ratio.

lockPlayerToCameraRotation.title: Lock Player To Camera Rotation
lockPlayerToCameraRotation.description: If selected the player will follow the camera rotation always, even stationary.

gamepadSprintThreshold.title: Gamepad Sprint Threshold
gamepadSprintThreshold.description: Set the threshold at which the gamepad joystick will switch from walking to sprinting.

deadZoneLow.title: Low Dead Zone
deadZoneLow.description: Radial thickness of inner dead zone of pad's joysticks. This dead zone ensures that all pads report a value of 0 for each joystick axis when untouched.

deadZoneHigh.title: High Dead Zone
deadZoneHigh.description: Radial thickness of outer dead zone of pad's joysticks. This dead zone ensures that all pads can reach the -1 and 1 limits of each joystick axis.

forwardEntity.title: Forward Entity
forwardEntity.description: You can optionally provide an entity to be used to calculate the forward direction when applying input to the controller. If no entity is provided then the model forward direction is used.

forceSwim.title: Force Swim
forceSwim.description: If selected the player will be forced to swim/float.

canMantle.title: Can Mantle
canMantle.description: If selected the player can mantle on edges and climb up.

jumpUpTimeout.title: Jump Up Timeout
jumpUpTimeout.description: Time required to reach the maximum jump elevation when jumping.

mantleRate.title: Mantle Rate
mantleRate.description: Controls how quickly the player mantles in place (should be synchronized with a corresponding animation).

cameraPositionInertia.title: Camera Position Inertia
cameraPositionInertia.description: Controls how quickly the camera snaps into position when following the player. Lower values give more "weight" to the camera. Set to 0.0 to disable any inertia.

cameraPivotInertia.title: Camera Pivot Inertia
cameraPivotInertia.description: Controls how quickly the camera snaps its point of view when following the player. Lower values give more "weight" to the camera. Set to 0.0 to disable any inertia.

customInputEvents.title: Custom Input Events
customInputEvents.description: Add custom input events to drive player input using app wide events. Requires application restart.

horizontalFov.title: Horizontal Fov
horizontalFov.description: Control the horizontal fov property of the player camera.

portraitFov.title: Portrait Fov
portraitFov.description: The camera field of view in portrait viewports.

landscapeFov.title: Landscape Fov
landscapeFov.description: The camera field of view in landscape viewports.

lockCameraToPlayerRotation.title: Lock Camera To Player Rotation
lockCameraToPlayerRotation.description: If selected the camera will follow the player rotation when the player is moving.

rotationInertia.title: Rotation Inertia
rotationInertia.description: The rotation time required for the character to turn towards the movement direction.

playerToPlayerCollision.title: Player to Player Collision
playerToPlayerCollision.description: If enabled players can collide with each other. Requires application reload.

footstepsParticles.title: Footsteps Particles
footstepsParticles.description: Reference an entity with a particlesystem component to fire automatically on certain footstep actions (start moving, jumping, landing, running).

gender.title: Gender
gender.description: The gender of the player model, used by the sound selector.

rotationStep.title: Rotation Step
rotationStep.description: Useful for creating a more retro 4 or 8 direction player rotation (set it to 45 or 90 for example).

jumpBoost.title: Jump Boost
jumpBoost.description: Multiplies the player jump speed to launch the player upwards.

scaleBoostByScale.title: Scale Boost By Scale
scaleBoostByScale.description: Scales the set jump boost by the object scale.

clampJumpBoost.title: Min Jump Boost
clampJumpBoost.description: Used to clamp to a min value the jump boost when scaled.

activeCameras.title: Active Cameras
activeCameras.description: A list of cameras that can be used for picking. Only the last enabled camera will be used each time.

playerEntities.title: Player Entities
playerEntities.description: A list of player entities that the picker event will fire on.

pickerEvent.title: Picker Event
pickerEvent.description: The entity event to fire on pick.

excludeEntities.title: Exclude Entities
excludeEntities.description: A list of entities to exclude from picking.

useRaycastAll.title: Use Raycast All
useRaycastAll.description: If selected the raycaster will do a raycastAll and return a list of entities instead of the first one. The list of entities will be sorted by distance and the first entity that matches all filters will be selected.

eventEntity.title: Event Holder
eventEntity.description: If an event entity is provided then all events will fire on that entity. Otherwise they will fire on the app object.

onRender.title: On Render
onRender.description: If an event name is provided the shader will update automatically when the event will fire. Useful when combining multiple effects on the same shader (e.g. terrain splatmaps with surface noise).

schema.name: timeOffset
schema.title: Time Offset
schema.description: You can set an optional time offset per channel to further randomize the wind animation.

schema.name: textureCoord
schema.title: Texture Coord
schema.description: Set which set of coordinates will be used to calculate the wind animation.

schema.name: textureCoordAxis
schema.title: Texture Coord Axis
schema.description: The axis on which the wind animation will play on. To use multiple axis you can add more channels.

schema.name: windBase
schema.title: Wind Base
schema.description: Set the starting coordinates value in the range of 0.0 to 1.0 for the wind animation.

schema.name: invertCoords
schema.title: Invert Coordinates
schema.description: If selected the coordinates used will be inverted.

windGustSize.title: Wind Gust Size
windGustSize.description: The size in world units of each  wind gust.

windDirection.title: Wind Direction
windDirection.description: The wind direction in the X and Z axis.

interactObject.title: Interact Object
interactObject.description: If selected the vertices of the model will be pushed away by any objects nearby.

interactList.title: Interact List
interactList.description: A list of entities that can interact with this material (on WebGL1 devices a maximum of 20 entities is supported).

interactRadius.title: Interact Radius
interactRadius.description: The area around each interaction entity that will be pushed away.

billboard.title: Billboard
billboard.description: If selected the model will be rendered as a billboard to always face the camera.

billboardLockY.title: Billboard Lock Y
billboardLockY.description: If set to true the billboard rotation will be only on Y axis, otherwise it will face the camera in all direction.

billboardRefSize.title: Billbaord Ref Size
billboardRefSize.description: Provide a list of render assets for each material (in the same order), to be used for sizing the billboard.

billboardReverseSize.title: Billboard Reverse Size
billboardReverseSize.description: If selected the billboard half extents calculation from the reference render asset will be reversed.

interactAxis.title: Interact Axis
interactAxis.description: Set the axis the vertext interact effect will be applied.

windTimeSpeed.title: Wind Time Speed
windTimeSpeed.description: Can be used to control the wind animation speed, works only with a local wind clock.

useLocalClock.title: Use Local Clock
useLocalClock.description: Spawn a local clock instead of using the global wind timer.

cellSize.title: Cell Size
cellSize.description: The size of the cell in the frustum culling grid. Only static instances support cell based culling. Minimum cell side size is 1.

updateFrequency.title: Update Frequency
updateFrequency.description: Set how often in seconds culling updates will execute for this cell. To disable this check and execute it per frame set it to 0.

updateShadowsFrequency.title: Update Shadows Frequency
updateShadowsFrequency.description: Set how often in seconds culling shadows updates will execute for this cell. To disable this check and execute it per frame set it to 0.

isDynamic.title: Is Dynamic
isDynamic.description: If selected all entities in each cell will update their world transform matrix. Useful for animating instances while in a cell. Note if an instanced changes its position to be outside its initial cell, it will not change cell automatically.

localPlayer.title: Local Player
localPlayer.description: The local player entity to track its position.

resetHeight.title: Reset Height
resetHeight.description: This is the height where the player loses and has to start over.

respawnDuration.title: Respawn Duration
respawnDuration.description: If a respawn checkpoint becomes available, the player has this much time to get back to it.

winHeight.title: Win Height
winHeight.description: This is the height where the player wins the game.

descendLoseDuration.title: Descend Lose Duration
descendLoseDuration.description: The minimum duration of a descend to consider losing (mainly plays a sound).

respawnOffsetHeight.title: Respawn Offset Height
respawnOffsetHeight.description: This controls when the respawn event will fire, by subtracting this offset height from the real checkpoint position.

belowGroundHeight.title: Below Ground Height
belowGroundHeight.description: To catch players when they fall through the ground.

reflectSkybox.title: Reflect Skybox
reflectSkybox.description: If selected the scene skybox will be added to the reflections.

reflectionLayers.title: Reflection Layers
reflectionLayers.description: The scene layers names that are being used by models casting reflections.

resolutionFactor.title: Resolution Factor
resolutionFactor.description: Used to scale down the resolution size of the reflection render target and improve performance. Set to 1 to be equal in size with the screen size. Set to 4 to downscale the resolution 4x.

activeCameras.title: Active Cameras
activeCameras.description: A list of cameras to render reflections from.

materialAssets.description: If apply shader is selected, this material will be updated to have the reflections map referenced on its diffuse channel. If not, a shader uniform named texture_planarReflectionMap will be added to the material scope.

reflectionVector.title: Reflection Vector
reflectionVector.description: If set to non zero, then this normal will be used instead of the entity back direction.

schema.name: applyShader
schema.title: Apply Shader
schema.description: If apply shader is selected, the referenced material will be updated to have the reflections map on its diffuse channel and the diffuse shader chunk will be updated.

schema.name: uvChannel
schema.title: UV Channel
schema.description: When using Apply Shader set which UV channel should be used.

schema.name: shaderReflectionsIntensity
schema.title: Reflections Intensity
schema.description: Sets the intensity of the reflections map.

schema.name: shaderReflectionsIndex
schema.title: Reflections Index
schema.description: Sets the reflection index that affects the reflections viewing angle.

schema.name: shaderReflectionsNormalMap
schema.title: Normal Map
schema.description: If a normal is provided it will be used for the reflections in the overriden shader.

schema.name: shaderReflectionsNormalIntensity
schema.title: Normal Intensity
schema.description: Sets the intensity of the reflections normal map.

schema.name: shaderReflectionsNormalTiling
schema.title: Normal Tiling
schema.description: Sets the UV tiling of the reflections normal map.

schema.name: shaderReflectionsMask
schema.title: Mask
schema.description: If a mask is provided it will be used to mask the reflections.

schema.name: shaderReflectionsMaskTiling
schema.title: Mask Tiling
schema.description: Sets the UV tiling of the reflections mask.

reflectionOffset.title: Reflection Offset
reflectionOffset.description: Add a reflection plane offset to fine adjust the exact position of the plane.

updateFrequency.title: Update Frequency
updateFrequency.description: Set the frequency of the reflections rendered to skip this number of frames. If it is set to 0 it will update per frame.

renderPreset.title: Render Preset
renderPreset.description: Select if a reflection or refraction map will be rendered (or both). Restart is required.

refractionLayers.title: Refraction Layers
refractionLayers.description: The scene layers names that iare being used by models casting refraction.

eventEntity.title: Event Holder
eventEntity.description: If an event entity is provided then all events will fire on that entity. Otherwise they will fire on the app object.

onRender.title: On Render
onRender.description: If an event name is provided the shader will update automatically when the event will fire. Useful when combining multiple effects on the same shader (e.g. terrain splatmaps with surface noise).

renderSurface.title: Render Surface
renderSurface.description: If a uranusEffectsRenderSurface entity is referenced the material diffuse color will be multiplied by the pixel color on that world position.

schema.name: noiseTexture
schema.title: Noise Texture
schema.description: Provide a noise sampling texture (grayscale).

schema.name: noiseTextureChannel
schema.title: Noise Texture Channel
schema.description: The channel to be used for the texture noise map.

schema.name: noiseTiling
schema.title: Noise Tiling
schema.description: The world tiling of the noise texture.

schema.name: noiseClamping
schema.title: Noise Clamping
schema.description: Clamp the noise intensity between a min and max value (0-1).

schema.name: noiseSpeed
schema.title: Noise Speed
schema.description: If a value > 0 is provided the noise texture will be animated, useful for wind effects.

schema.name: viewDistance
schema.title: View Distance
schema.description: If a view distance is provided the noise effect will gradually fade out after it's being reached.

schema.name: viewBorder
schema.title: View Border
schema.description: The view border size for the noise fade out effect.

schema.name: viewCamera
schema.title: View Camera
schema.description: If a camera entity is provided the view distance will be calculated from the entity world position. If none is provided then the world view position from the uranusInstancer will be used instead (this will work for instanced models only).

surfaceBlend.title: Surface Blend
surfaceBlend.description: If selected the pixel color will be blended up to the specified height with the surface, based on the rendered depth.

surfaceBlendHeight.title: Surface Blend Height
surfaceBlendHeight.description: If surface blend is enabled this value controls the blending height from the surface intersection.

surfaceBlendPower.title: Surface Blend Power
surfaceBlendPower.description: The power of the final surface blend color.

normalsBlend.title: Normals Blend
normalsBlend.description: If enabled the normals will be blended with the normals surface referenced in the normalsSurface attribute.

normalsSurface.title: Normals Surface
normalsSurface.description: If a uranusEffectsRenderSurface entity is referenced the material normal map will be derived from this surface. Make sure you are referencing a surface that rendered Normals.

surfaceNormalsBlendHeight.title: Surface Normals Blend Height
surfaceNormalsBlendHeight.description: If surface normals blend is enabled this value controls the blending height from the surface intersection.

surfaceNormalsBlendPower.title: Surface Normals Blend Power
surfaceNormalsBlendPower.description: The power of the final surface normals blend color.

schema.name: noiseTexture
schema.title: Noise Texture
schema.description: Provide a noise sampling texture (grayscale).

schema.name: noiseTextureChannel
schema.title: Noise Texture Channel
schema.description: The channel to be used for the texture noise map.

schema.name: noiseTiling
schema.title: Noise Tiling
schema.description: The world tiling of the noise texture.

schema.name: noiseClamping
schema.title: Noise Clamping
schema.description: Clamp the noise intensity between a min and max value (0-1).

playerEntity.title: Player Entity
playerEntity.description: The player entity to be animated across the path.

startEntity.title: Trigger Entity
startEntity.description: If a start entity is provided as a trigger to start the animation as soon as the player entity enters the trigger. A collision component is required to be attached.

animationDuration.title: Animation Duration
animationDuration.description: The total duration in seconds of the animation from start to end.

overrideAnimBoolean.title: Override Anim Boolean
overrideAnimBoolean.description: If an optional anim boolean parameter is provided, it will be automatically set to true on the anim component of the player entity. Useful to set a persisent animation state during the animation.

animateOnce.title: Animate Once
animateOnce.description: If selected the animation will play only once in the lifetime of this entity.

animateRotation.title: Animate Rotation
animateRotation.description: If selected the entity will directed to face towards the next point on the path.

rotationOffset.title: Rotation Offset
rotationOffset.description: To be used with animate once and apply a custom rotation offset after the look at is applied.

startEvent.title: Start Event
startEvent.description: If an app wide start event is provided the animation will start as soon as it fires.

curveType.title: Curve Type
curveType.description: The type of the animation curve used to interpolate between the animation points.

animationLoop.title: Animation Loop
animationLoop.description: If selected the animation will loop infinitely.

animationYoyo.title: Animation Yoyo
animationYoyo.description: If selected and Loop Animation is also selected the animation will yoyo back when looping.

endEvent.title: On End Event
endEvent.description: If an app wide end event is provided it will automatically fire each time the player entity reaches the end.

renderLine.title: Render Line
renderLine.description: If checked the line will be rendered in scene (works both in editor and on launch).

renderColor.title: Render Color
renderColor.description: The color of the line to render.

renderStep.title: Render Step
renderStep.description: The length of each line segment rendered.

isStatic.title: Is Static
isStatic.description: If checked the line will not update if any point gets updated (performance optimization).

autoStart.title: Auto Start
autoStart.description: Set it to true to automatically start the animation as soon as the entity is initialized. This property doesn't work in editor.

schema.name: time
schema.title: Time
schema.description: The time in seconds this event will fire on.

schema.name: event
schema.title: Event
schema.description: The app wide event name that will fire.

accelerationFactor.title: Acceleration Factor
accelerationFactor.description: Control the animation playback speed in realtime by updating this property.

pauseEvent.title: Pause Event
pauseEvent.description: If an app wide start event is provided the animation will pause as soon as it fires.

stopEvent.title: Stop Event
stopEvent.description: If an app wide start event is provided the animation will stop as soon as it fires.

resumeEvent.title: Resume Event
resumeEvent.description: If an app wide start event is provided the animation will resume as soon as it fires.

occlusionType.title: Occlusion Type
occlusionType.description: 1. Occluder: this entity will act as an occluder and obstruct occludees. 2. Occludee: this entity will act as an occludee and getting obstructed by occluders. A hardware occlusion query will execute for this entity based on its occlusion shape. The entity will be automatically change its visible status based on the query result.

occlusionShape.title: Occlusion Shape
occlusionShape.description: 1. Calculate Bounding: the script will automatically calculate the total bounding box of the model. 2. Collision Bounding: If a box collision component is provided that bounding box will be used. 3. Raw Geometry: No bounding box will be created, the raw geometry will be rendered in the Occlusion Layer. This provides accurate queries at the cost of performance. 4. None: The script will not add any model to the Occlusion Layer. Requires application restart.

isStatic.title: Is Static
isStatic.description: If selected the occluder will not update its position/rotation/scale per frame, this is a performance optimization.

behaviorResult.title: Behavior Result
behaviorResult.description: Controls what will happen When the occlusion query returns a new visibility state (works for Occludees only). 1. Visibility State: The model will change its visibility state. 2. Entity State: The entity will change its Enabled property. 3. Nothing will happen and only onEvent will fire if provided. Useful for gameplay only queries.

refEntities.title: Reference Entities
refEntities.description: Optionally provide one or more entities that this occludee is responsible for managing their state instead of this entity.

bypassInstancer.title: Bypass Instancer
bypassInstancer.description: If selected the occludee will toggle its model/render component instead of using the instancer to handle visibility.

onEvent.title: On Event
onEvent.description: If an event name is provided it will automatically fire on the pc.Application context when the visibility state changes.

starsScale.title: Stars Scale
starsScale.description: Set the scale of the stars on the sky.

starsBrightness.title: Stars Brightness
starsBrightness.description: Set the brightness of the stars on the sky.

cloudScale.title: Cloud Scale
cloudScale.description: Set the size of each individual cloud on the sky.

cloudBrightness.title: Cloud Brightness
cloudBrightness.description: Set the brightness of the clouds on the sky.

cloudOctaves.title: Cloud Octaves
cloudOctaves.description: The number of iterations to run for rendering the cloud shape. More octaves result in better quality at the expense of performance.

cloudNoise.title: Cloud Noise
cloudNoise.description: Provide a grayscale noise texture to be used as the base for the cloud pattern.

overrideHeight.title: Override Height
overrideHeight.description: If an entity is referenced here, that height will be used instead.

mixTextureA.title: Mix Texture A
mixTextureA.description: The texture to mix from based on the alpha value provided.

mixTextureB.title: Mix Texture B
mixTextureB.description: The texture to mix to based on the alpha value provided.

mixAlpha.title: Mix Alpha
mixAlpha.description: The alpha value used to mix the base and mix textures.

animateEvent.title: Animate Event
animateEvent.description: An app wide animation event that can be called with a true/false argument and animate the transition.

animateTime.title: Animate Time
animateTime.description: The time it takes to animate a full transition when the animate event is called.

resolution.title: Resolution
resolution.description: This defines how much the resolution will be downscaled or upscaled in relation to the viewport resolution. Leverage the browser bilinear filtering to increase performance by rendering your application in a lower resolution. Or render to a higher resolution for reducing anti alias.

customShape.title: Custom Shape
customShape.description: Select if a custom shape type will be created.

groupByScale.title: Group By Scale
groupByScale.description: Extends the default trimesh collider to support model scaling. Models should have a uniform scale and vary their scale from to another based on the step provided. This settings works only for trimesh shapes. If 0.0 is provided the regular PlayCanvas engine cache will be used instead.

playerEntity.title: Player Entity
playerEntity.description: If a player entity is provided the event will be attached to that entity, otherwise a global Application event will be used.

enableEvent.title: Enable Event
enableEvent.description: If an event is provided this element will be enabled as soon as this event fires.

inputEvent.title: Input Event
inputEvent.description: The event to fire on click.

eventEntity.title: Event Holder
eventEntity.description: If an event entity is provided then all events will fire on that entity. Otherwise they will fire on the app object.

onRender.title: On Render
onRender.description: If an event name is provided the surface will render automatically when the event will fire.

onSurface.title: On Surface
onSurface.description: If an event name is provided the rendered texture will be passed as a reference to the event callback. If no surface has been rendered, a new render will be scheduled.

shaderUniform.title: Shader Uniform
shaderUniform.description: If a uniform name is provided the rendered texture will be injected in the global WebGL context to be made accessible to all shaders.

layers.title: Layers
layers.description: A list of layer names which the render camera will target while rendering.

renderWidth.title: Render Width
renderWidth.description: The width of the render target.

renderHeight.title: Render Height
renderHeight.description: The height of the render target.

disableShadows.title: Disable Shadows
disableShadows.description: If selected shadows will be disabled for all lights during rendering.

disableLights.title: Disable Lights
disableLights.description: If selected all lights will be disabled during rendering. Only a single top down directional light will be added.

readPixels.title: Read Pixels
readPixels.description: If true, instead of returning the pc.Texture, a typed array with the image pixels will be returned.

cleanUpOnRender.title: Clean Up On Render
cleanUpOnRender.description: If true, the render target will automatically be destroyed after the render is complete and all events have fired.

debugOnScreen.title: Debug On Screen
debugOnScreen.description: If true, the rendered texture will be displayed on screen.

targetEntity.title: Target Entity
targetEntity.description: A target entity is required to size the camera viewport based on its model bounding box.

addLight.title: Add Light
addLight.description: If selected a top down directional light will be added.

elementEntity.title: Element Entity
elementEntity.description: If an entity with an image element component is provided, the rendered surface will be applied to it.

renderDepth.title: Render Depth
renderDepth.description: If selected a depth map will be rendered at the same time.

renderPreset.title: Render Preset
renderPreset.description: The selected preset to render with.

staticTimes.title: Static Times
staticTimes.description: Set the minimum shadow update time for each shadow cascade while the camera is stationary. Works only for PCF3 and PCF5 shadow casters.

movingTimes.title: Moving Times
movingTimes.description: Set the minimum shadow update time for each shadow cascade while the camera is moving. Works only for PCF3 and PCF5 shadow casters.

baseTime.title: Local Time
baseTime.description: Set the minimum shadow update time for all omni and spot lights casting shadows.

cullByShadowDistance.title: Cull By Shadow Distance
cullByShadowDistance.description: If selected point and spot lights will cull their shadows based from the light distance from the active camera.

activeCameras.title: Active Cameras
activeCameras.description: A list of cameras to be used for culling by shadow distance.

localLights.title: Local Lights
localLights.description: If selected local lights, omni and spot, will be handled too. Requires application restart.

dirLights.title: Dir Lights
dirLights.description: If selected directional lights will be handled. Requires application restart

activeCameras.title: Active Cameras
activeCameras.description: A list of entities to be used for calculating the state of the occludees from. Requires a collider together with a dynamic or kinematic rigidbody.

occluder.title: Occluder
occluder.description: Reference an entity with a collision component attached that will act as the occluder zone. When the active camera enters the zone, all occludees will be visible.

filters.title: Filters
filters.description: Optionally reference an entity with a collision component attached that will filter the occludees based on their world position. Any occludee outside of the collision trigger will be discarded and not parsed. Support collision shapes are box and sphere.

bypassInstancer.title: Bypass Instancer
bypassInstancer.description: If selected the occluder will toggle the model/render component instead of using the instancer to toggle visibility.

occludees.title: Occludees
occludees.description: A list of one or more entities to find occludees. Occludees will be any render component attached to them and on their children.

updateFrequency.title: Update Frequency
updateFrequency.description: Set the frequency of the cubemap renderer to skip this number of frames. If it is set to 1 it will update per frame. Set to 0 to pause rendering.

renderWidth.title: Render Width
renderWidth.description: The resolution of the render target for the cubemap. Updating it requires application reload.

prefilterCubemap.title: Prefilter Cubemap
prefilterCubemap.description: If selected the rendered cubemap will be filtered, required if used for reflections.

layers.title: Layers
layers.description: A list of layer names which the render camera will target while rendering.

materialAssets.title: Material Assets
materialAssets.description: If one or more materials are provided the environmental map will be applied to it, otherwise to the scene directly.

renderOnSkyTime.title: Render On Sky Time
renderOnSkyTime.description: This will automatically update the cubemap only when there is a sky time change.

renderOnce.title: Render Once
renderOnce.description: This will render the cubemap just once after it's enabled.

materialsTag.title: Materials Tag
materialsTag.description: Instead of referencing materials directly, you can use a tag to let the script find them on run time.

playerEntity.title: Player Entity
playerEntity.description: The player entity to be used to render the emojis on.

toggleKey.title: Toggle Key
toggleKey.description: Provide an optional key name to automatically toggle on/off the emoji on press.

emojiCategories.title: Emoji Categories
emojiCategories.description: If selected the emoji picker will include category tabs.

emojiSearch.title: Emoji Search
emojiSearch.description: If selected the emoji picker will include search.

emojiVariants.title: Emoji Variants
emojiVariants.description: If selected the emoji picker will include variants.

emojiRecents.title: Emoji Recents
emojiRecents.description: If selected the emoji picker will include recently selected emojis.

autoHide.title: Auto Hide
autoHide.description: If selected the emoji picker will be automatically hidden after an emoji is selected.

emojiPreview.title: Emoji Preview
emojiPreview.description: If selected the emoji picker will include a preview of the selected emoji.

emojiRecentsCount.title: Emoji Recents Count
emojiRecentsCount.description: The selected emoji picker recents count saved.

emojiSize.title: Emoji Size
emojiSize.description: The pixel size for each emoji in the picker.

emojiPerRow.title: Emoji Per Row
emojiPerRow.description: The number of emojis per row.

positionTop.title: Position Top
positionTop.description: The CSS top position of the emoji picker.

positionLeft.title: Position Left
positionLeft.description: The CSS left position of the emoji picker.

excludeEmojis.title: Exclude Emojis
excludeEmojis.description: A list of emojis to exclude from rendering (they will continue to be included in the emoji selector but they will not work).

animateTopPos.title: Animate Top Pos
animateTopPos.description: The top position in screen units to animate the emoji to.

animateDuration.title: Animate Duration
animateDuration.description: The time to show the emoji.

roomType.title: Room Type
roomType.description: The room type to connect on the server. It will either join an existing room or create a new one.

playerTemplates.title: Player Templates
playerTemplates.description: A list of template assets to spawn remote players from.

localPlayer.title: Local Player
localPlayer.description: The local player entity. The name of this entity will be used to track the right template to spawn from the Player Templates list in remote clients.

localRoom.title: Local Room
localRoom.description: If local is set to true the room will include only a specified world area. Entering/leaving that area will trigger room connect/disconnect events. A collision component is required to be set for that area.

areaId.title: Area ID
areaId.description: Define the room area ID to join or create a local instance of that room.

isMaster.title: Is Master
isMaster.description: If selected this room will become the active one when the client joins. Deselect for secondary parallel rooms like chat rooms.

updateFrequency.title: Update Frequency
updateFrequency.description: Set how many times per second the state of this player will be broadcasted to the server.

interpolationInertia.title: Interpolation Inertia
interpolationInertia.description: Sets how smoothly remote players will sync with the target states received. Lower values result in smoother interpolation at the expense of staying behind the remote state.

username.title: Username
username.description: Set an optional string based username.

activeCameras.title: Active Cameras
activeCameras.description: A list of cameras to be used for calculating the active LOD for this component. Only one enabled camera from the list will be used.

lodDistances.title: LOD Distances
lodDistances.description: Set the max distance from the active camera for each animation LOD level.

lodTimes.title: LOD Times
lodTimes.description: Set the animation update delay for each LOD level.

lodTimeout.title: LOD Timeout
lodTimeout.description: Set how often animation LOD calculations will take place. Set to 0.0 to execute them per frame (more expensive).

frustumCulling.title: Frustum Culling
frustumCulling.description: If enabled animation playback will pause when the bounding box is not in view.

boundingCenter.title: Bounding Center
boundingCenter.description: Set the center offset of the bounding sphere used for frustum culling.

boundingRadius.title: Bounding Radius
boundingRadius.description: Set the radius of the bounding sphere used for frustum culling.

hideDistance.title: Hide Distance
hideDistance.description: Set a distance threshold afterwards the model will be disabled/hidden. Set to 0.0 to always keep it visible.

avatar.title: Avatar
avatar.description: The avatar model parent entity used for this player controller.

snowThreshold.title: Snow Threshold
snowThreshold.description: The slope threshold to apply on each surface based on the pixel normal.

snowNoise.title: Snow Noise
snowNoise.description: A noise texture to make the transition towards snow more natural.

snowWaterLevel.title: Snow Water Level
snowWaterLevel.description: The Y axis position below which there will be no snow.

disableOnSkin.title: Disable On Skin
disableOnSkin.description: If selected no snow will be rendered on skinned (animated) models. Requires restart.

snowWaterBorder.title: Snow Water Border
snowWaterBorder.description: Affects the size of the snow border with the water level.

disableMaterialTag.title: Disable Material Tag
disableMaterialTag.description: Use this tag on your material assets to exclude them from rendering snow, when applying the effect globally.

materialAssets.title: Material Assets
materialAssets.description: If one or more materials are provided the effect will be only applied to these materials, instead of globally.

resolution.title: Resolution
resolution.description: Resolution of one side of a cubemap. Use power of 2 resolution if you wish to use Mipmaps.

mipmaps.title: Mipmaps
mipmaps.description: If set to true, mipmaps will be allocated and autogenerated.

depth.title: Depth
depth.description: If set to true, depth buffer will be created.

schema.name: index
schema.description: The LOD index for this level e.g. 0 for LOD0, 1 for LOD1.

schema.name: layer
schema.description: Add an optional layer name to specify a LOD level for this layer only. If left blank it will be used for any layer.

schema.name: layerType
schema.description: Set what type of payloads this LOD level will apply to. If left blank it will be used for any type.

schema.name: start
schema.description: Starting from this distance from the camera this level of detail will be visible.

schema.name: end
schema.description: After this distance from the camera this level of detail will be hidden. Use 0 to keep it enabled infinitely.

proxyMesh.title: Proxy Mesh
proxyMesh.description: If an entity is referenced, as soon as its model level of detail is visible, this entity model will be hidden. Useful for hierarchical LODs. The referenced entity needs to have an instanced model rendered.

skipShadowsLod.title: Skip Shadows LOD
skipShadowsLod.description: If selected all shadowcaster instances will skip any LOD check. Useful for rendering shadows for a lower level of detail, to lower polycount. You can control which LOD casts shadows by using the model/render component Cast Shadows property.

skipShadowsOffset.title: Skip Shadows Offset
skipShadowsOffset.description: If Skip Shadows LOD is selected you can define an offset on the Y axis to adjust the rendering position of the LOD shadowcaster. Useful for removing self shadowing artifacts when rendering shadows on a level of detail with a different polycount.

motionThreshold.title: Motion Threshold
motionThreshold.description: Number of meters moved in one frame before CCD is enabled

sweptSphereRadius.title: Swept Sphere Radius
sweptSphereRadius.description: This should be below the half extent of the collision volume. E.g For an object of dimensions 1 meter, try 0.2

contactProcessingThreshold.title: Contact Processing Threshold
contactProcessingThreshold.description:
This should be below the half extent of the collision volume. E.g For an object of dimensions 1 meter, try 0.2the constraint solver can discard solving contacts, if the distance is above this threshold. 0 by default. 
 Note that using contacts with positive distance can improve stability. It increases, however, the chance of colliding with degerate contacts, such as "interior" triangle edges

fixedTimeStep.title: Fixed Time Step
fixedTimeStep.description: Physics fixed time step, the number of times the physics engine step refreshes per second, changing this to more then 60 can effect performance

playerEntity.title: Player Entity
playerEntity.description: The player entity to be used to add sounds to.

playEvent.title: Play Event
playEvent.description: A global app wide event that can be used to fire custom sounds on the local player. Pass the slot name as an argument.

stopEvent.title: Stop Event
stopEvent.description: A global app wide event that can be used to fire custom sounds on the local player. Pass the slot name as an argument.

schema.name: title
schema.title: Title
schema.description: The title of the preset shown in the dialog.

schema.name: resolution
schema.title: Resolution
schema.description: This defines how much the resolution will be downscaled or upscaled in relation to the viewport resolution. Leverage the browser bilinear filtering to increase performance by rendering your application in a lower resolution. Or render to a higher resolution for reducing anti alias.

schema.name: devicePixelRatio
schema.title: Device Pixel Ratio
schema.description: A normalized value 0-1 to indicate min/max device pixel ratio.

schema.name: fogNoise
schema.title: Fog Noise
schema.description: Requires page reload.

schema.name: grass
schema.title: Grass
schema.description: Requires page reload.

startEntity.title: Start Entity
startEntity.description: If an entity is provided a start button will be created to enable that entity on user's action. The lobby entity will be disabled at the same time.

lobbyEntity.title: Lobby Entity
lobbyEntity.description: If an entity is provided the lobby entity will be enabled as soon as the settings dialog is enabled.

grassObjects.title: Grass Objects
grassObjects.description: A list of entities to be disabled if grass is disabled in settings.

minTerrainLod.title: Min Terrain Lod
minTerrainLod.description: The minimum terrain LOD when no shadows are cast from the terain.

terrainEntities.title: Terrain Entities
terrainEntities.description: If one or more terrain entities are provided, they will be binded to the terrain shadows toggle.

autoSelectPreset.title: Auto Select Preset
autoSelectPreset.description: If selected a graphics preset will automatically be selected based on the device platform.

playerControllers.title: Player Controllers
playerControllers.description: One or more player controllers to be used with the Toggle Controller button.

defaultController.title: Default Controller
defaultController.description: The default controller the game will start with.

schema.name: minPreset
schema.title: Min Preset
schema.description: Preset to fall back to if minimum FPS threshold is crossed. Leave blank to disable the check.

schema.name: minFps
schema.title: Min FPS
schema.description: The minimum FPS limit.

schema.name: minTime
schema.title: Min Time
schema.description: The time in seconds the FPS should be lower than the limit to force a downgrade.

schema.name: startTime
schema.title: Start Time
schema.description: The time in seconds counting from the application start the downgrade check should be enabled. Set to 0 to keep it always enabled.

playerEntity.title: Player Entity
playerEntity.description: The player controller entity used to hold this avatar. It will be used to check if it is a local vs remote player. If none is provided this will be a local avatar and the character selection screen will show.

readyPlayerMeUrl.title: Ready Player Me Url
readyPlayerMeUrl.description: Subdomain used to connect to the Ready Player Me API (without trailing slash). Request access here: https://readyplayer.me

applyMaterials.title: Apply Materials
applyMaterials.description: A list of Uranus scripts to apply avatar materials to the materialAssets attribute, if available. Useful to quickly reference runtime generated materials.

layers.title: Layers
layers.description: A comma separated list of layer names to apply to the loaded avatar model. If none is provided the default PlayCanvas layers are added.

clearParent.title: Clear Parent
clearParent.description: If selected the parent entity will be cleared of any other entities. Useful when using a local player model as placeholder while loading the remote avatar.

autoStart.title: Auto Start
autoStart.description: If selected the character selection screen will be automatically shown.

useLocalStorage.title: Use Local Storage
useLocalStorage.description: If selected the selected character will be saved in the local storage. In future sessions the avatar will be automatically loaded from there.

selectionWidth.title: Selection Width
selectionWidth.description: The screen percentage width size of the character selection window.

selectionHeight.title: Selection Height
selectionHeight.description: The screen percentage height size of the character selection window.

textureFormat.title: Texture Format
textureFormat.description: Reduce avatar file size by formatting all textures into the specified format. Using webp encoding can result in up to 40% reduction in avatar file size.

localLod.title: Lod (local)
localLod.description: Control the triangle count of the entire avatar for the local player.

remoteLod.title: Lod (remote)
remoteLod.description: Control the triangle count of the entire avatar for remote players.

localTextureSizeLimit.title: Texture Size Limit (local)
localTextureSizeLimit.description: Set the upper limit for texture resolution in pixels of any texture in the avatar.

remoteTextureSizeLimit.title: Texture Size Limit (remote)
remoteTextureSizeLimit.description: Set the upper limit for texture resolution in pixels of any texture in the avatar.

localTextureAtlas.title: Texture Atlas (local)
localTextureAtlas.description: Generate a texture atlas of the desired resolution. This operation merges all meshes and splits opaque objects from transparent ones resulting in a maximum of 2 draw calls. The texture atlas is generated for all PBR channels - baseColor, normal, metallicRoughness, emissive, and occlusion, if any of the assets making up the avatar includes them.

remoteTextureAtlas.title: Texture Atlas (remote)
remoteTextureAtlas.description: Generate a texture atlas of the desired resolution. This operation merges all meshes and splits opaque objects from transparent ones resulting in a maximum of 2 draw calls. The texture atlas is generated for all PBR channels - baseColor, normal, metallicRoughness, emissive, and occlusion, if any of the assets making up the avatar includes them.

localTextureChannels.title: Texture Channels  (local)
localTextureChannels.description: Select the texture channels you want to have included in the .glb. (By default, the .glb comes with all available channels). You can combine these values by comma separation: baseColor,normal,metallicRoughness,emissive,occlusion,none

remoteTextureChannels.title: Texture Channels (remote)
remoteTextureChannels.description: Select the texture channels you want to have included in the .glb. (By default, the .glb comes with all available channels). You can combine these values by comma separation: baseColor,normal,metallicRoughness,emissive,occlusion,none

dracoCompression.title: Draco Compression
dracoCompression.description: Select if draco compression should be used on the avatar model.

frustumCulling.title: Frustum Culling
frustumCulling.description: Controls the culling of instances against the camera frustum (frustum culling needs to enabled on each camera component). If false all instances will be rendered regardless of their visibility. Changing this setting requires application reload.

cloneMaterials.title: Clone Materials
cloneMaterials.description: If selected all instances will use a clone of the original model material. This is useful when the original material is being used in non instanced models and otherwise it will produce render artifacts. Changing this setting requires application reload.

disableCells.title: Disable Cells
disableCells.description: Disable cells generation and do per instance culling globally. In editor this setting is being bypassed for entities to allow for individual editing.

disableShadows.title: Disable Shadows
disableShadows.description: If selected no shadows buffers will be created (optimization). Requires app reload.

bypassTransparent.title: Bypass Transparent
bypassTransparent.description: If selected transparent mesh instances will not be instanced.

excludeTag.title: Exclude Tag
excludeTag.description: Use this tag on entities to exclude them from instancing.

shadowsOnlyTag.title: Shadows Only Tag
shadowsOnlyTag.description: Use this tag on entities to exclude them from model rendering. Those models will only render shadows.

entityDisableTag.title: Entity Disable Tag
entityDisableTag.description: Use this tag on entities to exclude them from rendering their model. It will be rendered only for shadows.

excludeLayers.title: Exclude Layers
excludeLayers.description: Mesh instances rendered in these layers won't be instanced.

schema.name: index
schema.description: The LOD index for this level e.g. 0 for LOD0, 1 for LOD1.

excludeShadowsLayers.title: Exclude Shadows Layers
excludeShadowsLayers.description: Payloads in these layers will skip generating shadow casters.

materialShadowsDisable.title: Material Shadows Disable
materialShadowsDisable.description: Use this tag on material assets to exclude them from rendering shadows.

materialCloneDisable.title: Material Clone Disable
materialCloneDisable.description: Use this tag on material assets to exclude them from cloning their material.

lodMultiplier.title: LOD Multiplier
lodMultiplier.description: The LOD multiplier all LOD Levels start/end distances will be multiplied with. Useful when creating LOD presets.

autoDynamicCells.title: Auto Dynamic Cells
autoDynamicCells.description: If this is selected the instancer will attempt to automatically understand if an instance has moved in a cell and update it accordingly. It can have a performance hit with too many cells/instances

schema.name: cellSize
schema.title: Cell Size
schema.description: The size of the cell in the frustum culling grid. Only static instances support cell based culling. Minimum cell side size is 1.

schema.name: updateFrequency
schema.title: Update Frequency
schema.description: Set how often in seconds culling updates will execute for this cell. To disable this check and execute it per frame set it to 0.

schema.name: updateShadowsFrequency
schema.title: Update Shadows Frequency
schema.description: Set how often in seconds culling shadows updates will execute for this cell. To disable this check and execute it per frame set it to 0.

schema.name: isDynamic
schema.title: Is Dynamic
schema.description: If selected all entities in each cell will update their world transform matrix. Useful for animating instances while in a cell. Note if an instanced changes its position to be outside its initial cell, it will not change cell automatically.

excludeCellsTag.title: Exclude Cells Tag
excludeCellsTag.description: Use this tag to exclude entities from being included in the global cells, if used.

forceTransparentTag.title: Force Transparent Tag
forceTransparentTag.description: Use this tag on entities with transparent materials to force them to be included when the Bypass Transparent flag is used.

templates.title: Templates
templates.description: A list of templates that random instances will be spawned from.

dataHolder.title: Data Holder
dataHolder.description: If an entity that has an uranusInstancerData script attached is referenced, instead of spawning entities in the hierarachy, data will be saved on it.

parentEntity.title: Parent Entity
parentEntity.description: All instances spawned will be added as children to that entity. If none is provided, then this painter entity will be used instead.

brushSize.title: Brush Size
brushSize.description: The size of the brush where instances will be spawned. If 0 is provided instances will be spawned at the exact raycast point.

brushDistance.title: Brush Distance
brushDistance.description: The distance between each brush stroke instances will be spawned.

instancesPerStroke.title: Instances Per Stroke
instancesPerStroke.description: The min/max number of instances to be spawned per stroke.

positionOffset.title: Position Offset
positionOffset.description: An offset to be applied to the instance position.

projectOffset.title: Project Offset
projectOffset.description: If enabled the offset will be projected to the final calculated scale of the instance.

randomRotation.title: Random Rotation
randomRotation.description: Randomnly rotate each instance on the selected axis.

alignSurface.title: Align Surface
alignSurface.description: If selected the instance will be aligned on the surface normal.

scaleMinMax.title: Scale Min/Max
scaleMinMax.description: Set the minimum and maximum allowed random scale to be applied.

validSurfaces.title: Valid Surfaces
validSurfaces.description: A list of entities that are valid targets for the painting brush. If none is provided, all surfaces are valid.

rotationOffset.title: Rotation Offset
rotationOffset.description: An offset to be applied to the instance rotation.

projectScale.title: Project Scale
projectScale.description: If enabled the scale will be multiplied with initial scale of the instance.

gltfAsset.title: glTF Asset
gltfAsset.description: Reference a gltf asset that includes the data to parse (rename to .json before uploading).

selection.title: Selection
selection.description: If a parent entity is referenced here, only its descendant entities will be processed.

colorChangeTicks.description: How many ticks are given for the color change warning and how many ticks the color change lasts.

offsetStart.title: Offset Start
offsetStart.description: The start offset used to calculate the final position.

offsetEnd.title: Offset End
offsetEnd.description: The end offset used to calculate the final position.

duration.title: Duration
duration.description: The time required to go from start to end position.

schema.name: idle
schema.title: idle
schema.description: idle: waiting on the spot.

schema.name: approach
schema.title: approach
schema.description: approach: moving towards the closest player.

schema.name: attackMelee
schema.title: attackMelee
schema.description: attackMelee: execute a melee attack when in player proximity.

schema.name: interact
schema.title: interact
schema.description: execute player interact state.

schema.name: hit
schema.title: hit
schema.description: execute player hit state.

schema.name: die
schema.title: die
schema.description: execute player die state.

behaviors.title: Behaviors
behaviors.description: The states this NPC can cycle between.

initialBehavior.title: Initial Behavior
initialBehavior.description: Set the starting behavior for this character.

updateFrequency.title: Update Frequency
updateFrequency.description: Set how many times per second the object behavior will be evaluated.

schema.name: behavior
schema.title: Behavior
schema.description: The behavior this set of locomotion params relate to.

schema.name: speed
schema.title: Speed
schema.description: The speed when moving towards the target.

schema.name: targetOffset
schema.title: Target Offset
schema.description: Set an optional min/max offset from target position to randomize paths. Useful when multiple NPCs follow the same player.

schema.name: stopDistance
schema.title: Stop Distance
schema.description: The distance from target to stop moving.

schema.name: exitTime
schema.title: Exit Time
schema.description: Setting an Exit Time for this behavior will lock it and it will remain active despit any other conditions. Set to 0.0 to disable this check.

schema.name: exitBehavior
schema.title: Exit Behavior
schema.description: If Exit Time is used you can set optionally an Exit Behavior to automatically select on exit.

pivotDistance.title: Pivot Distance
pivotDistance.description: The max distance from the initial starting position (pivot) this state can be selected. Moving further away will revert to the Initial Behavior. Set to 0.0 to disable this check.

raycastGround.title: Raycast Ground
raycastGround.description: If selected the object will raycast downwards and adjust it's position on Y based on the surface hit.

raycastOffsetY.title: Raycast Offset Y
raycastOffsetY.description: The offset on Y from this entity pivot point to start the raycast from. It provides control over what kind of objects it can traverse.

raycastInertiaY.title: Raycast Inertia Y
raycastInertiaY.description: Controls how fast/slow the player will snap on Y based on the raycast hit.

ownershipClaim.title: Ownership Claim
ownershipClaim.description: Set how ownership for this object should be claimed by players.

ownershipEvent.title: Ownership Event
ownershipEvent.description: Optionally set a custom entity event that can be fired to claim ownership. The player entity claiming ownership should be passed as first argument.

ownershipDistance.title: Ownership Distance
ownershipDistance.description: Set the maximum distance this object can be from the player that claimed ownership. Getting further away will automatically drop ownership. Set to 0.0 to disable this check.

schema.name: enabled
schema.title: Enabled
schema.description: Replicate the entity enabled state.

schema.name: position
schema.title: Position
schema.description: Replicate the entity position.

schema.name: rotation
schema.title: Rotation
schema.description: Replicate the entity rotation.

schema.name: scale
schema.title: Scale
schema.description: Replicate the entity scale.

schema.name: linearVelocity
schema.title: Linear Velocity
schema.description: Replicate the entity rigidbody linear velocity.

schema.name: angularVelocity
schema.title: Angular Velocity
schema.description: Replicate the entity rigidbody angular velocity.

schema.name: animState
schema.title: Anim State
schema.description: Replicate the entity anim base layer current state.

schema.name: destroy
schema.title: Destroy
schema.description: Replicate the entity destroy event (once).

replicate.title: Replicate
replicate.description: Choose the various states to replicate across the network. The state persists between players joining and leaving.

updateFrequency.title: Update Frequency
updateFrequency.description: Set how many times per second the state of this object will be broadcasted to the server.

interpolationInertia.title: Interpolation Inertia
interpolationInertia.description: Sets how smoothly remote objects will sync with the target states received. Lower values result in smoother interpolation at the expense of staying behind the remote state.

ownershipTags.title: Ownership Tags
ownershipTags.description: A list of tags a player entity must have to be able to claim ownership.

ownershipSleep.title: Ownership Sleep
ownershipSleep.description: If selected and the object is a rigidbody, the owner will be cleared as soon as the body sleeps.

singleOwner.title: Single Owner
singleOwner.description: If selected ownership can't be claimed over existing owners, only if no owner exists.

schema.name: name
schema.title: Name
schema.description: The property name.

schema.name: value
schema.title: Value
schema.description: The property value.

schema.name: event
schema.title: Event
schema.description: Provide an entity event name to automatically fire each time the property value changes.

customProperties.title: Custom Properties
customProperties.description: A list of custom property values to replicate. You can use an entity event with this signature to update its value: "uranusControllerNetworkObject:propertyUpdate:my-property-name" and pass the new value as the first argument.

initialState.title: Initial State
initialState.description: Set the enabled state of the entity after initialization, useful to disable the entity but allow this script to initialize and connect.

usePlayerGuid.title: Use Player Guid
usePlayerGuid.description: If a player entity is referenced instead of using a world pos based guid instead the player network ID plus the entity name will be used to form the guid.

replicateOnInit.title: Replicate On Init
replicateOnInit.description: If enabled the state of the object will be broadcasted and replicated on init.

prependOnGuid.title: Prepend On Guid
prependOnGuid.description: Append a string on the generated guid, useful to track objects on the server.

syncRenderState.title: Sync Render State
syncRenderState.description: If selected and a render component is attached to this entity, the enabled state will also toggle the render component enabled state.

debug.description: If enabled any particle system used will not be cloned, useful for debugging particle effects on the main player.

maxLOD.description: The maximum LOD level for which to spawn particles.

active.title: Active
active.description: Set the state of the effect.

priority.title: Priority
priority.description: Set the loading priority. Lower numbers will load first.

schema.name: singleItem
schema.description: If selected only a single item from this category can be active.
